Residential estates are next on the City of Tshwane’s hot list. It's been cutting off power supply for default customers. Courtesy of #DStv403 TSHWANE - Residential estates are next on the City of Tshwane’s hot list. It's been cutting off power supply for default customers. READ: Court action over Tshwane disconnections The city said it will continue disconnecting businesses and other government agencies owing money. The City of Tshwane's Jordan Griffiths said, "our intention is to continue with disconnections next week and the comings weeks.it will be targeting residential estates, businesses and other government agencies….. "What we will also do is mop up operations in areas we have been too: the recurring issue is that people reconnect the areas illegally….what we also do is introduce rip connections, if you have tempered with infrastructure is that we rip out your entire electricity box so you do not reconnect. We will be doing a bit of that in the coming week." R150-million. That's how much the City of Tshwane says it's collected since Tuesday. This after it switched off water and electricity to its big defaulters in the municipality. Tshwane has however received backlash from some clients who have threatened to take it to court. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu has more. Courtesy #DStv403